'''阿凯·格里枪杀案'''于2014年11月20日发生在美国，[[纽约市|纽约市]][[布鲁克林区|布鲁克林区]]。事件造成了28岁的黑人阿凯·格里（Akai Gurley）的死亡。开枪者是[[纽约市警察局|纽约市警察局]]的一名亚裔警官彼得·梁（Peter Liang）, 时年27岁。<div>事件发生时，两名纽约市警察局的警官正在布鲁克林区东纽约区的一幢公寓内沿着楼梯巡逻。这幢名叫“路易斯·H·平克”的公寓属于纽约市城市公寓管理局管理。两名警官中的一名，彼得·梁，在巡逻的时候将自己的配枪掏出并握在了手中。此时格里和他的女朋友正位于7楼的楼梯上，位置低于两名警官14级台阶。彼得·梁据说因受到惊吓而开枪，射击事件被定性为意外走火，子弹在经过墙壁反弹后射入了格里的胸部。格里后来在医院中去世。<ref name="New York Times">{{Cite news|last1 = Izadi|first1 = Elahe|last2 = Holley|first2 = Peter|title = Officer’s Errant Shot Kills Unarmed Brooklyn Man|url = http://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/22/nyregion/new-york-police-officer-fatally-shoots-brooklyn-man.html|accessdate = 26 November 2014|publisher = New York Times Post|date = 21 November 2014|archive-date = 2021-03-10|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210310042603/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/22/nyregion/new-york-police-officer-fatally-shoots-brooklyn-man.html|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="nydailynews.com">{{Cite news|url = http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/brooklyn/nypd-officer-guns-man-28-brooklyn-housing-project-article-1.2018724|title = Panicked rookie NYPD officer fatally shoots unarmed 28-year-old man in Brooklyn's Pink Houses project|newspaper = NEW YORK DAILY NEWS|date = 21 November 2014|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2021-01-23|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210123083642/https://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/brooklyn/nypd-officer-guns-man-28-brooklyn-housing-project-article-1.2018724|dead-url = no}}</ref></div>

2015年2月10日，梁警官被大陪审团（七男五女）<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/former-nypd-cop-peter-liang-s-guilty-verdict-leaves-community-n518056|title=Former NYPD Cop Peter Liang's Guilty Verdict Leaves a Community Divided|newspaper=NBC News|accessdate=2017-05-10|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112020415/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/former-nypd-cop-peter-liang-s-guilty-verdict-leaves-community-n518056|dead-url=no}}</ref>观看了平克大楼的漆黑的监控录像和轮流使用作案工具（9mm 的手枪）<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nypost.com/2016/01/26/liang-had-thousand-yard-stare-after-staircase-shooting-fellow-cop-testifies/|title=Liang had ‘thousand-yard stare’ after staircase shooting, fellow cop testifies|accessdate=2017-05-10|date=2016-01-26|last=Saul|first=Emily|work=New York Post|archive-date=2020-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200930165907/https://nypost.com/2016/01/26/liang-had-thousand-yard-stare-after-staircase-shooting-fellow-cop-testifies/|dead-url=no}}</ref>之后发现它的扳机需要11.5磅的力量，判定手枪没有走火之后<ref name=":0" />，以[[误杀|误杀]]、故意伤害和其他刑事罪名（总共五项）<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2016/02/akai-gurley-verdict/462471/|title=A Guilty Verdict in the Akai Gurly Case|last=Phippen|first=J. Weston|newspaper=The Atlantic|accessdate=2017-05-10|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210311234119/https://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2016/02/akai-gurley-verdict/462471/|dead-url=no}}</ref>起诉。<ref name="MyUser_Newyork.cbslocal.com_February_11_2015c">{{Cite web|url = http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2015/02/10/wcbs-880-rookie-nypd-officer-peter-liang-indicted-in-fatal-shooting-of-akai-gurley-family-attorney-says/|title = NYPD Officer Peter Liang Indicted In Fatal Shooting Of Akai Gurley « CBS New York|newspaper = Newyork.cbslocal.com|date = |author = |accessdate = February 11, 2015|archive-date = 2020-02-02|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200202124802/https://newyork.cbslocal.com/2015/02/10/wcbs-880-rookie-nypd-officer-peter-liang-indicted-in-fatal-shooting-of-akai-gurley-family-attorney-says/|dead-url = no}}</ref>他于第二天自首并等待调查。2016年2月11日，梁警官被认定误杀和渎职两项罪名成立<ref name="Carrega">{{Cite web|author = Carrega-Woodby, Christina; Marzulli, John; Brown Stephen Rex|url = http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/nyc-crime/nypd-peter-liang-guilty-fatal-shooting-akai-gurley-article-1.2528827|title = NYPD Officer Peter Liang found guilty of manslaughter in fatal shooting of Akai Gurley in Brooklyn housing development|publisher = ''[[New_York_Daily_News|New York Daily News]]''|date = February 11, 2016|accessdate = February 11, 2016|archive-date = 2021-01-30|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210130190904/https://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/nyc-crime/nypd-peter-liang-guilty-fatal-shooting-akai-gurley-article-1.2528827|dead-url = no}}</ref>。他当时将可能面临15年不到的监禁。美国华裔平等权益协会副主席[[彭礼琨|彭礼琨]]（{{lang-en|Kevin Peng}}）在白宫请愿网站发起撤回对梁刑事指控请愿签名，该请愿签名超过了12万，超过了白宫需对此请求做出回应的10万个签名的门槛。<ref name="#1">{{cite news|author1=中国新闻网|title=纽约华裔警察被控谋杀 多地华社酿示威|url=http://news.sohu.com/20150225/n409139486.shtml|date=2015-02-25|accessdate=2017-10-11|archive-date=2020-01-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200114061852/http://news.sohu.com/20150225/n409139486.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>該判決也引起了部分美国华人的抗議。他们大量使用社交软件微信<ref name="#2">{{Cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/world/asia/la-fg-china-liang-protests-20160224-story.html|title=Chinese social media platform plays a role in U.S. rallies for NYPD officer|last=Makinen|first=Julie|date=2016-02-24|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|accessdate=2017-04-23|language=en-US|issn=0458-3035|archive-date=2021-05-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210504215020/https://www.latimes.com/world/asia/la-fg-china-liang-protests-20160224-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，连带少量的脸书，电子邮件和推特去联合<ref name="#2"/>，并且约定于当月22日在全国多个城市或地区举行游行，同时死者的支持者也举行抗议活动。梁警官对这一判罚提起上诉。<ref name="NBC News">{{cite news|last1=Fuchs|first1=Chris|title=Former NYPD Cop Peter Liang's Guilty Verdict Leaves a Community Divided|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/former-nypd-cop-peter-liang-s-guilty-verdict-leaves-community-n518056|accessdate=17 February 2016|publisher=NBC News|date=13 February 2016|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112020415/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/former-nypd-cop-peter-liang-s-guilty-verdict-leaves-community-n518056|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2016年4月19日，布鲁克林高等法院法官Danny K. Chun判决梁警官5年缓刑和800小时社区服务，将其“误杀”罪名降级，但“渎职”罪名不作改变。此举引起阿凯·格里的支持者不满，并再次举行抗议活动。而梁警官的支持者则认为此次事件中没有胜利者<ref name=sentence></ref>。

== 事件背景 ==

=== 彼得·梁 ===
彼得·梁（{{lang-en|Peter Liang}}，1987－）是一名華裔美国人，已婚。事件发生时，他在[[纽约市警察局|纽约市警局]]工作不足18个月。他出生于香港，并在幼时随父母移民美国<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://thesaltcollective.org/indictment-peter-liang/|title = On the Indictment of Peter Liang|first = Liz|last = Lin|newspaper = The Salt Collective|accessdate = 2016-04-26|archive-date = 2020-08-13|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200813052027/https://thesaltcollective.org/indictment-peter-liang/|dead-url = no}}</ref>。事发前与父母和祖母住在布鲁克林区本森赫斯特<ref>[http://mobile.nytimes.com/2015/02/12/nyregion/officers-indictment-in-akai-gurleys-death-brings-little-solace-to-brooklyn-residents.html?_r=0&referrer= Officer's indictment brings little solace] {{Wayback|url=http://mobile.nytimes.com/2015/02/12/nyregion/officers-indictment-in-akai-gurleys-death-brings-little-solace-to-brooklyn-residents.html?_r=0&referrer= |date=20190713065448 }}, [[纽约时报|New York Times]]</ref>。梁的父亲是一名厨师，母亲则在制衣厂工作。梁毕业于[[曼哈頓華埠|纽约中国城]]的M.S.131学校。他被认为有很多黑人朋友，也经常与他们在学校内一起参体育活动。梁还有一个弟弟目前在大学读书<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.worldjournal.com/2153314/article-%E6%A2%81%E5%BD%BC%E5%BE%97%E9%9D%9E%E8%A3%94%E6%9C%8B%E5%8F%8B%E5%A4%9A-%E4%B8%8D%E6%9B%BE%E6%AD%A7%E8%A6%96/?ref=%E7%B4%90%E7%B4%84|title = 梁彼得非裔朋友多 不曾歧視|newspaper = World Journal 世界日报|date = 14 February 2015|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150705080808/http://www.worldjournal.com/2153314/article-%E6%A2%81%E5%BD%BC%E5%BE%97%E9%9D%9E%E8%A3%94%E6%9C%8B%E5%8F%8B%E5%A4%9A-%E4%B8%8D%E6%9B%BE%E6%AD%A7%E8%A6%96/?ref=%E7%B4%90%E7%B4%84|archivedate = 2015年7月5日|accessdate = 2016年2月16日}}</ref>。据称，梁在很小的时候就立志成为一名警察<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.worldjournal.com/2091698/article-%E4%BB%96%E7%9C%9F%E7%9A%84%E5%BE%88%E5%A5%BD-%E9%84%B0%E5%B1%85%E7%82%BA%E6%A2%81%E5%BD%BC%E5%BE%97%E5%8F%AB%E5%B1%88/?ref=%E7%B4%90%E7%B4%84|title = 他真的很好 鄰居為梁彼得叫屈|newspaper = World Journal 世界日报|date = 12 February 2015|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://archive.is/20150221193539/http://www.worldjournal.com/2091698/article-%E4%BB%96%E7%9C%9F%E7%9A%84%E5%BE%88%E5%A5%BD-%E9%84%B0%E5%B1%85%E7%82%BA%E6%A2%81%E5%BD%BC%E5%BE%97%E5%8F%AB%E5%B1%88/?ref=%E7%B4%90%E7%B4%84|archivedate = 2015年2月21日|accessdate = 2016年2月16日}}</ref>。

=== 阿凯·格里 ===
阿凯·格里（{{lang-en|Akai Gurley}}，1986－2014年11月20日）出生于[[加勒比地区|加勒比地区]]的[[聖托馬斯島_(美屬維爾京群島)|美属维京群岛的圣托马斯]]，幼时便搬到了纽约生活<ref name="prgm">Akai Kareem Gurley's funeral service program, Dec. 6, 2014, Brown Memorial Baptist Church, Brooklyn</ref>。事发时，他和女友及一名2岁的女儿住在路易斯·H·平克公寓。他有24次被捕的记录，这其中有一部分是由于参与了销售毒品<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2014/11/21/nypd-investigating-fatal-police-involved-shooting-inside-brooklyn-housing-complex/|title = Bratton: Fatal Police-Involved Shooting of Unarmed Man at Brooklyn Housing Complex ‘Unfortunate Tragedy’|publisher = CBS New York|accessdate = 11 April 2015|date = November 21, 2014|archive-date = 2020-11-11|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201111204456/https://newyork.cbslocal.com/2014/11/21/nypd-investigating-fatal-police-involved-shooting-inside-brooklyn-housing-complex/|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url = http://nypost.com/2014/11/21/man-killed-by-rookie-cop-planned-to-surprise-mom-in-florida/|title = Man killed by NYPD rookie planned to surprise mom in Florida|work = New York Post|accessdate = 11 April 2015|date = November 21, 2014|last1 = Saul|first1 = Josh|archive-date = 2020-12-12|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201212100412/https://nypost.com/2014/11/21/man-killed-by-rookie-cop-planned-to-surprise-mom-in-florida/|dead-url = no}}</ref>。

=== 事发地点 ===
根据纽约市巡警权益协会警官帕特里克·林奇的描述：“路易斯·H·平克公寓是纽约市最危险的建筑物之一，而其楼梯又是整幢楼中最危险的区域。”<ref name="infear">{{Cite news|url = http://nypost.com/2014/11/22/tenants-live-in-fear-at-the-notorious-pink-houses/|title = Living in fear at the dark & deadly hellhole houses|work = New York Post|accessdate = 11 April 2015|author = Ben Feuerherd|author2 = Lorena Mongelli|author3 = Sophia Rosenbaum|date = November 22, 2014|archive-date = 2021-05-05|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210505040328/https://nypost.com/2014/11/22/tenants-live-in-fear-at-the-notorious-pink-houses/|dead-url = no}}</ref>就在最近，路易斯·H·平克公寓就发生了数起犯罪事件。[[警察總監|警察总监]]比尔·布莱顿证实在本事件前的一个月内，这桩楼中就发生了2起谋杀、2起抢劫和4次枪击案件<ref name="infear"/><ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/12/10/akai-gurley-vertical-patrols_n_6263202.html|title = Akai Gurley's Death Shines Harsh Light On Vertical Patrols In Public Housing|work = The Huffington Post|accessdate = 11 April 2015|author = Christopher Mathias|date = December 10, 2014|archive-date = 2018-10-26|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20181026194839/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/12/10/akai-gurley-vertical-patrols_n_6263202.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>。

== 枪杀过程 ==
两名新手警察被安排去执行巡查由纽约市城市公寓管理局所管理的一間楼房"路易斯·H·平克公寓"。在巡查过程中，他们被报告说违反了警局指令，执行了被称作“竖直巡逻”的行为<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/brooklyn/exclusive-texted-union-rep-akai-gurley-lay-dying-article-1.2034219|title=EXCLUSIVE: Rookie NYPD officer who shot Akai Gurley in Brooklyn stairwell was texting union rep as victim lay dying|date=2014-12-05|accessdate=2016-02-15|archive-date=2021-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210510091949/https://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/brooklyn/exclusive-texted-union-rep-akai-gurley-lay-dying-article-1.2034219|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title = Akai Gurley, Unarmed Man, Shot By NYPD|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/11/22/akai-gurley-nypd_n_6205492.html|newspaper = Huffington Post|date = 22 November 2014|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2016-03-04|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304065109/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/11/22/akai-gurley-nypd_n_6205492.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>。竖直巡逻時，警察自上而下巡查整个[[公營住宅|廉租屋]]，在每层都做停留以观察是否有犯罪行为发生<ref name="cry">{{Cite news|url = http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2014/dec/pfig06/akai-gurleys-funeral-a-cry-for-answers|title = Akai Gurley's funeral: a cry for answers|newspaper = The Guardian|first = Oliver|last = Laughland|date = 5 December 2014}}</ref>。

[[警察總監|警察总监]]比尔·布莱顿认为纽约市警局关于是否在巡逻时应该把枪保持在枪套中的规定被故意制定的十分模糊，是否拔枪完全由当事警察自己决定<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://nypost.com/2014/11/22/rookie-cops-often-assigned-to-dangerous-vertical-patrols/|title = Rookie cops often assigned to dangerous ‘vertical patrols’|newspaper = New York Post|date = 22 November 2014|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2020-09-23|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200923125135/https://nypost.com/2014/11/22/rookie-cops-often-assigned-to-dangerous-vertical-patrols/|dead-url = no}}</ref>。

当时28岁的阿凯·格里正在拜访他的女朋友并打算在[[感恩节|感恩节]]之前将头发辫起来。当时他的身上并没有武器。他从两名警察，肖恩·兰道尔和彼得·梁所处位置的一层楼以下进入了楼梯间，据说是因为电梯坏了。当时两名警察正在沿着漆黑的楼道对整个建筑进行巡查。根据检察官所述，梁警官的惯用手是左手，他当时将[[9×19mm魯格彈|格洛克手枪]]拿在左手并用右手拿着手电筒。当时，他用右肩撞开了楼梯间的门并将脸转向左边，对着7楼的楼梯间，也就是格里进入的位置。官方表示，似乎双方都不知道彼此的存在，在枪击发生之前也没有进行任何的语言交流<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.wsj.com/articles/nypd-officer-surrenders-after-indictment-in-death-of-unarmed-man-1423668909|title = NYPD Officer Pleads Not Guilty in Shooting Death of Unarmed Man|newspaper = The Wall Street Journal|date = 11 February 2015|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2021-05-20|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210520031516/https://www.wsj.com/articles/nypd-officer-surrenders-after-indictment-in-death-of-unarmed-man-1423668909|dead-url = no}}</ref>。梁警官后来表示，当时由于他受到了“来自左方的巨大声响”的惊吓，在开门的过程中不小心扣动了扳机，子弹在经过墙壁反弹后射入了格里的胸部，这一发子弹撕裂了他的心脏。他的女友当时在场并试图救他。911在事后放出的录音（youtube上可搜到）显示，格里倒在了5楼，一位女性（疑为邻居？）报警，而在报警过程中格里已失去呼吸（其女友哭喊“他没有呼吸了！”）而接线生试图教格里的女友对格里进行CPR。而在场两位警官均未成功对其进行CPR抢救。格里随后在医院去世<ref name="New York Times"/><ref name="nydailynews.com"/>。也有报道指出，格里在听到枪声后就开始逃跑，并没有注意到自己正在流血，直到最后倒在了5楼<ref name="nydailynews.com" />。 

== 与蒂莫西·斯坦斯伯里二世枪杀案的相似处 ==
阿凯·格里的死亡和此前发生在2004年1月蒂莫西·斯坦斯伯里枪杀案十分相似。那起案件造成了19岁的蒂莫西·斯坦斯伯里二世在位于布鲁克林的路易斯·阿姆斯特朗公寓屋顶被枪击而死亡。当时大约是凌晨1点，理查德·S·奈里警官正在持枪检查公寓的楼道。陪审团拒绝以过失致死的罪名起诉奈里警官。在听取了奈里警官关于自己受到惊吓从而无意中开枪的证词后，陪审团表示这件事是一个意外。<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/22/nyregion/new-york-police-officer-fatally-shoots-brooklyn-man.html?_r=0|title = Officer’s Errant Shot Kills Unarmed Brooklyn Man|newspaper = New York Times|date = 21 November 2014|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2020-11-25|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201125023802/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/22/nyregion/new-york-police-officer-fatally-shoots-brooklyn-man.html?_r=0|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/lupica-shooting-doesn-east-new-york-ferguson-article-1.2021103|title = Lupica: Shooting of Akai Gurley doesn't make East New York into Ferguson, or officer into a criminal|newspaper = New York Daily News|date = 23 November 2014|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2020-09-28|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200928162724/https://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/lupica-shooting-doesn-east-new-york-ferguson-article-1.2021103|dead-url = no}}</ref>

== 被用以作比较的案件 ==
在2014年八月九日，[[麥可·布朗命案|迈克尔·布郎]]在未携带武器的情况下被白人警察达伦·威尔逊枪杀。布朗并无犯罪记录。与警察的接触少于三分钟。

这起事件引发连续多日的抗议行动，甚至出现暴动，警方派出大量警员、装甲车，并发射了催泪瓦斯和橡皮子弹试图平息骚乱，FBI也已经介入调查。在8月16日，为了维持当地治安，州长杰伊·尼克松（Jay Nixon）宣布当地进入[[紧急状态|紧急状态]]，从午夜到上午五点间将实施[[宵禁|宵禁]]。

达伦·威尔逊最后判决无罪。

在2014年7月17日警察用15秒致使[[埃里克·加纳死亡案|埃里克]]窒息死亡。2014年12月3日，[[大陪审团|大陪审团]]决定不起诉潘特雷昂。事件引发民众抗议和集会指控警察滥用私刑。截至2014年12月28日，全国范围内至少有50场针对加纳的示威游行，同时有数百场示威游行以普通警察暴力加纳为切入点。

丹尼尔·潘塔雷昂最后被判决无罪。

== 后续发展 ==
纽约警局警察总监比尔·布莱顿表示这个事件是一个意外，格里是“无辜的”<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/22/nyregion/new-york-police-officer-fatally-shoots-brooklyn-man.html?referrer=|title = Officer’s Errant Shot Kills Unarmed Brooklyn Man|newspaper = NY Times|date = 22 November 2014|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2020-02-04|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200204001522/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/22/nyregion/new-york-police-officer-fatally-shoots-brooklyn-man.html?referrer=|dead-url = no}}</ref>。布魯克林區检察官肯·汤姆森（Kenneth P. Thompson）表示他计划开始组成陪审团来调查阿凯·格里的死亡<ref name="New York Times"/><ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/10/nyregion/high-expectations-for-brooklyn-prosecutor-in-handling-of-fatal-police-shooting.html|title = A Police Killing Puts Heavy Expectations on a Prosecutor|date = 9 December 2014|first = Stephanie|last = Clifford|newspaper = NY Times|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2021-04-12|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210412033010/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/10/nyregion/high-expectations-for-brooklyn-prosecutor-in-handling-of-fatal-police-shooting.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>。

纽约市市长白思豪对法院判决结果并没有任何主观的看法，只在接受采访时表示这是一个让所有人伤心的悲剧。在垂直巡查这个问题上，白思豪表示它是必须的存在的，它存在着才可以更好的保护市民的安全。白思豪对亚裔澄清，表明了彼得·梁并不是替罪羊。白思豪还向黑人澄清，表示所有的案件都是独立存在的，并没有任何相关的联系。<ref name="#3">{{Cite news|url=http://www.politico.com/states/new-york/city-hall/story/2016/02/de-blasio-doubts-liang-conviction-will-have-chilling-effect-on-police-031248|title=De Blasio doubts Liang conviction will have chilling effect on police|newspaper=Politico PRO|accessdate=2017-04-21|archive-date=2021-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210118121345/https://www.politico.com/states/new-york/city-hall/story/2016/02/de-blasio-doubts-liang-conviction-will-have-chilling-effect-on-police-031248|dead-url=no}}</ref>

