=== 重视黑人生命运动 ===
格里的死亡事件成为“重视黑人生命”运动抗议示威的一部分<ref>{{Cite web|last1 = Prupis|first1 = Nadia|title = NYPD Officer Indicted in Shooting of Akai Gurley: Reports|url = http://www.commondreams.org/news/2015/02/10/nypd-officer-indicted-shooting-akai-gurley-reports|publisher = [[Common_Dreams_NewsCenter|Common Dreams NewsCenter]]|accessdate = May 26, 2015|archive-date = 2021-03-06|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210306195023/https://www.commondreams.org/news/2015/02/10/nypd-officer-indicted-shooting-akai-gurley-reports|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = A statement from members of the #BlackLivesMatter team|url = https://www.facebook.com/BlackLivesMatter/posts/369845739853344|accessdate = May 25, 2015|archive-date = 2020-06-05|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200605180654/https://www.facebook.com/BlackLivesMatter/posts/369845739853344|dead-url = no}}</ref>。 2014年23月27日，尽管纽约市市长呼吁推迟示威活动，还是有约200名群众游行至[[布鲁克林大桥|布鲁克林大桥]]，抗议格里被杀。当天也是之前遇害的纽约市警员拉斐尔·拉莫斯（Rafael Ramos）的葬礼<ref name="MyUser_Https:_January_4_2015c"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2016/01/08/n-y-police-shooting-that-has-divided-chinese-americans-will-be-tried-by-jury/|title=NY police shooting that has divided Chinese Americans will be tried by jury|last1=Wang|first1=Yanan|newspaper=Washington Post|date=2016-01-08|accessdate=2016-04-01|archive-date=2020-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200706064119/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2016/01/08/n-y-police-shooting-that-has-divided-chinese-americans-will-be-tried-by-jury/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=npr2/>。

=== 纽约市警察局 ===
一些亚裔团体内部的评论家相信梁警官是由于其亚裔的身份才受到了当前的判罚，如果他是一名白人，他就会被判处无罪<ref>{{cite web|title=Peter Liang is unlucky to be an Asian New York cop|url=http://atimes.com/2016/02/peter-liang-is-unlucky-to-be-an-asian-new-york-cop/|accessdate=15 February 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160215160028/http://atimes.com/2016/02/peter-liang-is-unlucky-to-be-an-asian-new-york-cop/|archivedate=2016年2月15日}}</ref>。 纽约市警局也受到了一些关于没能提供当事警察足够训练和派遣两名新警察巡逻危险区域的指责。梁警官的律师也指出，梁警官在射击之后受到了极度的惊吓，并且认为由于警察学校没能够提供必要的训练，自己没有能力给格里提供心肺复苏的急救，所以他没有第一时间抢救格里。梁警官事发时的同伴，肖恩·兰道尔（被不予起诉），也作证说他没有受到过足够的急救训练<ref>{{cite web|title=Officer Liang’s Partner Testifies He Got Little CPR Training|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/05/nyregion/officer-liangs-partner-testifies-he-got-little-cpr-training.html|accessdate=4 February 2016|archive-date=2021-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422025722/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/05/nyregion/officer-liangs-partner-testifies-he-got-little-cpr-training.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。不止如此，带领他和梁的教授还故意作弊让他们全部通过急救训练。

== 法律诉讼 ==
2015年2月10日，由于造成格里的死亡，梁警官被以二级误杀、[[過失致死|过失致人死亡]]、二级袭击、疏忽致险和其他两项渎职的罪名起诉。梁警官被要求在2月11日出庭受审，他在那天向警方自首<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.ny1.com/nyc/all-boroughs/news/2015/02/10/officer-indicted-in-shooting-death-of-akai-gurley.html|title = Officer Indicted in Shooting Death of Akai Gurley|date = 10 February 2015|newspaper = NY1|first = Lori|last = Chung|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2018-03-02|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180302221442/http://www.ny1.com/nyc/all-boroughs/news/2015/02/10/officer-indicted-in-shooting-death-of-akai-gurley.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>。他在法庭上表示不认罪，随后被释放。法庭并没有要求其提供保释金。同天，他被纽约市警局停职停薪。 如果被判决有罪，梁警官将面临最高15年的刑期。2016年1月25日，庭审正式开始。2016年2月11日，他被判决误杀和渎职的罪名成立<ref name="Carrega"/>。

另一名涉事的警官肖恩·兰道尔没有因此事件被起诉<ref name=npr2>{{cite web|url=http://www.npr.org/sections/codeswitch/2015/05/14/406444625/n-y-police-shooting-case-divides-citys-asian-americans|title=NY police shooting case divides Asian American|date=2015-05-14|accessdate=2016-04-01|first=Hansi|last=Wang|newspaper=NPR|archive-date=2021-03-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210312045501/https://www.npr.org/sections/codeswitch/2015/05/14/406444625/n-y-police-shooting-case-divides-citys-asian-americans|dead-url=no}}</ref>。但是，在梁警官被定罪以后第二天，他就被纽约市警局开除。和梁警官一样，兰道尔警官也处于两年的试用期内，且被开除时，试用期尚未结束。由于同意在梁警官的庭审中作证，兰道尔被免于起诉。兰道尔形容事发时梁警官“十分震惊”，“（梁警官）难以相信他枪击了别人”。兰道尔表示他和梁警官都没有尝试抢救格里，因为他们都认为自己不具有执行心肺复苏的资质。据称是因为他和梁一起毕业的学院里面，他们的指导人员给他们作弊，让他们过关的。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2016/02/akai-gurley-verdict/462471/|title=A Guilty Verdict in the Akai Gurly Case|last=Phippen|first=J. Weston|newspaper=The Atlantic|accessdate=2017-04-20|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210311234119/https://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2016/02/akai-gurley-verdict/462471/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在格里的女朋友实施心肺复苏时，两人都用无线电呼叫了救护车<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abc7ny.com/news/nypd-officer-testifies-at-manslaughter-trial-of-his-former-partner-peter-liang/1187138/|title=NYPD OFFICER TESTIFIES AT MANSLAUGHTER TRIAL OF HIS FORMER PARTNER, PETER LIANG|accessdate=2016-04-01|date=2016-02-04|first=TIM|last=FLEISCHER|newspaper=ABC|archive-date=2016-03-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160317081518/http://abc7ny.com/news/nypd-officer-testifies-at-manslaughter-trial-of-his-former-partner-peter-liang/1187138/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mobile.nytimes.com/2016/02/13/us/politics/police-department-fires-partner-of-ex-officer-peter-liang.html?referer=https://www.google.com/|title=Police department fires partner of ex-officer Peter Liang|accessdate=2016-04-01|date=2016-02-12|first=ASHLEY|last=SOUTHALL|newspaper=New York Times|archive-date=2019-07-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190713065449/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/13/us/politics/police-department-fires-partner-of-ex-officer-peter-liang.html?referer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2F|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2016年3月28日，布鲁克林区检察官肯·汤普森（Kenneth Thompson）提议梁警官只需以软禁在家的方式服刑。<ref name=bet>{{cite news|url=http://www.bet.com/news/national/2016/03/28/brooklyn-district-attorney-recommends-former-nypd-officer-peter-.html/|title=Bratton: District Attorney Recommends Former NYPD Officer Peter Liang Only Get House Arrest for Killing Unarmed Akai Gurley|date=2016-03-28|accessdate=2016-04-06|first=Reggie|last=Wade|archive-date=2020-08-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200815053955/https://www.bet.com/news/national/2016/03/28/brooklyn-district-attorney-recommends-former-nypd-officer-peter-.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2016年4月19日，布鲁克林高等法院法官Danny K. Chun判决梁警官5年缓刑和800小时社区服务。Chun法官表示：“当我在录像中看到被告走进平克公寓的大堂时，我不得不注意到他心中所想的是为了保护这里的居民；”“他从未想过枪杀他人，这不是有意为之的；”“我认为让梁警官入狱并没有必要。与其在家中服刑，我认为他更应该参与到社区服务中。”<ref name=sentence>{{cite web|url=http://nypost.com/2016/04/19/nypd-cop-peter-liang-gets-community-service-for-killing-akai-gurley/?utm_medium=SocialFlow&utm_campaign=SocialFlow&utm_source=NYPFacebook&utm_term=breakingnews_exclusives|title=NYPD cop Peter Liang gets community service for killing Akai Gurley|accessdate=2016-04-19|date=2016-04-19|first=Emily|last=Saul|newspaper=New York Post|archive-date=2020-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200204001648/https://nypost.com/2016/04/19/nypd-cop-peter-liang-gets-community-service-for-killing-akai-gurley/?utm_medium=SocialFlow&utm_campaign=SocialFlow&utm_source=NYPFacebook&utm_term=breakingnews_exclusives|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 法院里的争论点 ==
地区助理检察官<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/nyc-crime/nypd-peter-liang-didn-realize-gurley-shot-lawyer-article-1.2525596|title=Prosecutor rips Peter Liang's defense in Akai Gurley killing|newspaper=NY Daily News|accessdate=2017-05-11|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210304044735/https://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/nyc-crime/nypd-peter-liang-didn-realize-gurley-shot-lawyer-article-1.2525596|dead-url=no}}</ref> 约瑟夫 亚历克西斯, 指责梁故意杀人—梁选择将他的手指放在扳机上. 不过雷 科谢茨 持有相反意见。她坚持这件事只是一起悲剧，而不是一起刑事案件。因为子弹是射在墙上而被反弹出去的。并且 罗伯特 布朗和 雷 科谢茨还争论梁是处于震惊状态，无法感知到子弹射中了任何人。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/former-nypd-cop-peter-liang-s-guilty-verdict-leaves-community-n518056|title=Former NYPD Cop Peter Liang's Guilty Verdict Leaves a Community Divided|newspaper=NBC News|accessdate=2017-05-11|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112020415/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/former-nypd-cop-peter-liang-s-guilty-verdict-leaves-community-n518056|dead-url=no}}</ref> 被告还争论道 取枪是完全符合规矩的，因为“没有光线是被默认为有犯罪活动的”<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.motherjones.com/politics/2016/03/peter-liang-police-conviction-nypd|title=Why was Peter Liang one of so few cops convicted for killing an unarmed man?|newspaper=Mother Jones|accessdate=2017-05-11|language=en|archive-date=2017-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170409225944/http://www.motherjones.com/politics/2016/03/peter-liang-police-conviction-nypd|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

不过原告指责梁渎职，因为他在案发后并没有对死者实施抢救，而是向他的上级打报告，寻求帮助<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bing.com/cr?IG=D34C9F443F8F465B9B8237085A7BE54F&CID=25D382FBCD8A617D1D028888CC1A60BF&rd=1&h=rViIM5iGEV7oC60Ty9L0FuJgzljb9uIDFJNUPIPOLV0&v=1&r=http://news.ifeng.com/a/20160221/47518860_0.shtml&p=DevEx,5083.1|title=梁彼得事件引华人社区分裂 律师：勿用中国思维看美国司法_凤凰资讯|accessdate=2017-05-11|work=www.bing.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2016/03/peter-liang-police-shooting/471687/|title=Why Was Officer Peter Liang Convicted?|last=Phippen|first=J. Weston|newspaper=The Atlantic|accessdate=2017-05-11|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210509234406/https://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2016/03/peter-liang-police-shooting/471687/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 结尾 ==
纽约市以大约四百万美元的赔偿与格里的家庭达成和解。纽约住房管理局赔偿大约四十万美元，前警察彼得梁赔偿两万五千美元。 所有的钱将会给与阿凯拉，格里的两岁女儿。但是阿凯拉在十八岁之前不会有渠道去使用这些钱。不过要是她可以得到法庭的允许，她可以使用它们。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/new-york-city-peter-liang-pay-4-1-million-settlement-n631736|title=New York City, Peter Liang to Pay Over $4 Million Settlement to Family of Akai Gurley|newspaper=NBC News|accessdate=2017-05-04|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108105755/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/new-york-city-peter-liang-pay-4-1-million-settlement-n631736|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/civil-suit-dismissed-peter-liang-expected-not-appeal-conviction-n677046|title=As civil suit dismissed, Peter Liang expected to not appeal conviction|newspaper=NBC News|accessdate=2017-05-04|language=en|archive-date=2020-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200204001717/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/civil-suit-dismissed-peter-liang-expected-not-appeal-conviction-n677046|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在梁与格里家庭和解之后， 大约二十六万美元基金被送还给捐者。大约三十二万五千美元基金被捐给梁的家庭。大约八万美元会花在华人社区。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://voicesofny.org/2016/12/where-do-funds-raised-for-peter-liang-go/|title=– Where Do Funds Raised for Peter Liang Go?|accessdate=2017-05-04|work=voicesofny.org|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180804045853/https://voicesofny.org/2016/12/where-do-funds-raised-for-peter-liang-go/|archive-date=2018-08-04|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

== 媒体报道 ==
这件事情得到了全国和世界媒体的广泛关注。部分原因是由于这件事距离之前几起警察射杀黑人的案件时间上很接近。这些事件包括：发生在 2014 年八月的 [[密苏里州|密苏里州]][[弗格森_(密蘇里州)|弗格森市]]的[[邁克爾·布朗命案|邁克爾·布朗命案]]、2014 年七月的[[纽约市|纽约市]][[史泰登岛|史坦顿岛]]的[[埃里克·加纳死亡案|埃里克·加纳死亡案]]和弗格森市的骚乱事件。<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/recent-police-killings-cited-protests-27770701|title = A Look at Recent Police Killings Cited in Protests|date = 22 December 2014|website = ABC News|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2015-01-05|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150105072914/http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/recent-police-killings-cited-protests-27770701|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title = Like Michael Brown And Eric Garner, Akai Gurley's Death Inspires Anger|newspaper = NPR|url = http://www.npr.org/2014/12/05/368768521/like-michael-brown-and-eric-garner-akai-gurleys-death-inspires-anger|first = Stephen|last = Nessen|date = 5 December 2014|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2020-02-02|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200202124306/https://www.npr.org/2014/12/05/368768521/like-michael-brown-and-eric-garner-akai-gurleys-death-inspires-anger|dead-url = no}}</ref>

纽约市警局的“竖直巡逻”行为也受到了批评<ref>{{Cite news|title = Lessons From a Stairwell Shooting|url = http://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/03/opinion/lessons-from-a-stairwell-shooting.html?referrer=|newspaper = NY Times|date = 2 December 2014|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2020-02-02|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200202124302/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/03/opinion/lessons-from-a-stairwell-shooting.html?referrer=|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title = Akai Gurley's Death Shines Harsh Light On Vertical Patrols In Public Housing|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/12/10/akai-gurley-vertical-patrols_n_6263202.html|newspaper = Huffington Post|date = 10 December 2014|first = Christopher|last = Mathias|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2018-10-26|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20181026194839/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/12/10/akai-gurley-vertical-patrols_n_6263202.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>。《乡村之声》杂志形容这个事件是纽约市警局一整年以来与公众关系灾难的一部分。<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://blogs.villagevoice.com/runninscared/2014/12/a_year_in_fails_the_nypd_is_so_not_media-savvy.php|title = The Year in NYPD Public Relations Disasters|newspaper = The Village Voice|first = Kathie|last = Toth|date = 19 December 2014|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141220212414/http://blogs.villagevoice.com/runninscared/2014/12/a_year_in_fails_the_nypd_is_so_not_media-savvy.php|archivedate = 2014年12月20日|accessdate = 2016年2月16日}}</ref>其他的媒体还关注了公寓的管理与维护和公共安全问题在这件事情中的影响<ref>{{Cite news|title = Let’s take the longer view on NYCHA’s safety|url = http://amsterdamnews.com/news/2014/dec/19/lets-take-longer-view-nychas-safety/|newspaper = New York Amsterdam News|date = 19 December 2014|first = Gregory|last = Floyd|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2014-12-21|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141221000146/http://amsterdamnews.com/news/2014/dec/19/lets-take-longer-view-nychas-safety/|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title = After Akai Gurley: The Connection Between Maintenance and Safety in Public Housing|url = http://thebrooklynink.com/2014/12/18/54307-after-akai-gurley-the-connection-between-maintenance-and-safety-in-public-housing/|newspaper = The Brooklyn Ink|first = Asaf|last = Shalev|date = 18 December 2014|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141220221822/http://thebrooklynink.com/2014/12/18/54307-after-akai-gurley-the-connection-between-maintenance-and-safety-in-public-housing/|archivedate = 2014年12月20日|df = |accessdate = 2016年2月16日}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title = I-Team: Darkened Stairwell Not the Only Problem at Police Shooting Building|url = http://www.nbcnewyork.com/investigations/akai-gurley-pink-houses-NYCHA-Darkened-Stairwell-Police-Shooting-Scene-285867111.html|newspaper = NBC New York|date = 16 December 2014|accessdate = 2016-02-16|archive-date = 2019-12-06|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191206191441/https://www.nbcnewyork.com/investigations/akai-gurley-pink-houses-NYCHA-Darkened-Stairwell-Police-Shooting-Scene-285867111.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>。

== 其他的影响 ==
在星期五，二月十二号，2016年，格里的家庭发起了一个联合诉讼，要求纽约警察局永久结束所有的垂直巡查并且停止使用纽约警察局作为安全保障。在这之上，他们还要求把梁的同事，兰道尔，停职。格里的家庭还要求城市重新管理资金，将那些用来增长警察基层的资金用在其他地方， 像是“经济适用房，”“社区中心”还有“校后节目。”<ref name="#3"/>

